@page "/"

<PageTitle>Catalog Editor</PageTitle>

<h1>Catalog Editor</h1>

<p>Welcome to the MCP Estimator Catalog Editor. Use this application to manage your project estimation catalog.</p>

<div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title"><span class="bi bi-people-fill"></span> Roles</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Manage implementation roles with Copilot productivity multipliers.</p>
                <a href="/roles" class="btn btn-primary">Manage Roles</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title"><span class="bi bi-box-fill"></span> Countables</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Define countable items that contribute to project scope.</p>
                <a href="/countables" class="btn btn-primary">Manage Countables</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title"><span class="bi bi-gear-fill"></span> Features</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Manage typical work items and technical activities.</p>
                <a href="/features" class="btn btn-primary">Manage Features</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3 mb-3">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title"><span class="bi bi-list-nested-nav-menu"></span> Catalog</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Map features to role estimates using t-shirt sizing.</p>
                <a href="/catalog" class="btn btn-primary">Manage Catalog</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-info mt-4">
    <h5>About the Catalog</h5>
    <p>
        This catalog stores all configuration in a timestamped JSON file at <code>data/catalogs/catalog-{timestamp}.json</code>.
        Each catalog entry stores <strong>Medium (M) baseline estimates</strong> for each role, and other t-shirt sizes
        (XS, S, L, XL) are calculated using Fibonacci scaling.
    </p>
</div>
